					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Looks like the graphics are doing what they should be.  The question seems to be how to write more than 256 bytes, am I right?
<br />
<br />If so, you use a pointer with indirect addressing like "lda (pointer_in_zeropage),y"
<br />
<br />the pointer is made and used like this:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">ptr_lo = $00 ; must be low, then high<br />ptr_hi = $01<br /><br />lda #&gt;background<br />sta ptr_hi<br />lda #&lt;background<br />sta ptr_lo<br /><br />ldy #0<br />ldx #4 ; copy 4 pages of 256 bytes<br />@back<br />lda &#40;ptr_lo&#41;,y<br />sta $2007<br />iny<br />bne @back<br />inc ptr_hi<br />dex<br />bne @back<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
